            "id": "4540686",
            "title": "Sens. Warren, Durbin demand documents on Powell investigation - report",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Sens. Elizabeth Warren (D-M) and Dick Durbin (D-IL) are demanding that officials of the Trump administration submit records tied to the Justice Department's criminal investigation of Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell, according to a Tuesday media report.</p>\n<p>Earlier in the month, federal prosecutors <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4538237-federal-prosecutors-open-criminal-investigation-into-fed-chair-powell---nyt\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"opened a criminal probe\">opened a criminal probe</a> into Powell over the Fed's renovation of its Washington headquarters and whether Powell lied to Congress about the project’s scope. Powell subsequently <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4538239-powell-says-subpoenas-are-result-of-not-cutting-rates-for-trump\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"asserted\">asserted</a> that the grand jury subpoenas served by the DOJ are not about legitimate legal concerns, but rather punishment for the central bank’s refusal to set interest rates according to President Donald Trump’s preferences.</p>\n<p>In letters sent to Attorney General Pam Bondi and to Federal Housing Finance Agency Director Bill Pulte, Warren and Durbin wrote they want the Trump officials to preserve any documents related to the Powell probe and send them to the Senate, the <em>Wall Street Journal</em> reported.</p>\n<p>The senators <a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/politics/democratic-senators-demand-records-on-powell-probe-75ad7d99?gaa_at=eafs&amp;gaa_n=AWEtsqf3Tq1bSsHOwJ4bSA9CS8We-bqiGr3E-ufekSrmlAgBlZrGRj3_kYtsGT1T-0o%3D&amp;gaa_ts=696feb4c&amp;gaa_sig=3d6bs8SC53PXG20pSA_CQE_wjPHqgUNVbytkfLtxyZon9vS0ucnNvLhkyCSZL0IkDujLPNixxCcjdvO_P7OMcA%3D%3D\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"wrote\">wrote</a> that \"the investigation appears to be a serious misuse of power,\" the <em>WSJ </em>reported, citing the letter to Pulte. This marks the first formal congressional response to the subpoena served on the Fed earlier this month.</p>\n<p>An FHFA spokesperson told the newspaper that the DOJ falls outside of Pulte's regulatory purview. </p>\n<p>The White House didn't immediately respond to Seeking Alpha's request for comment.</p>\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-726958da-7fff-31f5-b6ed-62a429f67598\">Dear readers: </strong>We recognize that politics often intersects with the financial news of the day, so we invite you to <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/article/4857703-politics-and-the-markets-012026\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"click here\">click here</a> to join the separate political discussion.</p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
