            "title": "Murphy Oil plunges after exploration well off Ivory Coast disappoints",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Murphy Oil (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MUR\" title=\"Murphy Oil Corporation\">MUR</a></span>) closed <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">-10.4%</span> on Tuesday after reporting its Civette-1X exploration well offshore Côte d’Ivoire reached a total depth of 13,950 ft and encountered <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20368496-murphy-oil-corporation-announces-results-of-civette-exploration-well-in-cote-d-ivoire\" target=\"_self\" title=\"non-commercial hydrocarbons\">non-commercial hydrocarbons</a> across multiple intervals.</p>\n<p><span dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">The probe was Murphy's (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MUR\" title=\"Murphy Oil Corporation\">MUR</a>) </span><span dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">fi</span><span dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">rst in a multi-well </span><span dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">exploration campaign in the West African country.</span></p>\n<p><span dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Murphy (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MUR\" title=\"Murphy Oil Corporation\">MUR</a>) holds a 90% working interest in Block CI-502 offshore Côte d'Ivoire and serves as operator, and state-owned Petroci owns 10%; the partners said they will continue their exploration program by drilling the Caracal and Bubale prospects, which they said have significant resource potential.</span></p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
